node.text:
Introducing The Origami Family, a collection of origami figures created by Swedish designer @claravonzweigbergk in collaboration with HAY. These pieces, all handmade by von Zweibergk herself, will be available for a limited time only, launching 16 September during @3daysofdesign and sold exclusively at HAY House (Copenhagen).

#HAY #HAYdesign

node.title: The Origami Family by Clara von Zweigbergk for HAY

node.text:
The new design collaboration with the world-renowned Belgian design duo Muller Van Severen is now available. Celebrated around the world for their minimal elegance, Muller Van Severen bring their eye for colour and their affinity for simplicity that eschews the ordinary to their creations. For HAY, Muller Van Severen have designed the Arcs Lamp Shades, the Arcs Candleholder, the Arcs Vase, and the Two-Colour Table (the latter dropping in November).

@mullervanseveren #HAY #HAYdesign

node.text: Introducing the New Order Configurator, a professional tool that allows you to envision and design the perfect New Order system to suit your needs! Use the tool to access all of New Order's innumerable components, customize combinations of functional elements, select colours and materials, get prices and item lists, and finally download and save your designs! @stefandiez #HAY #HAYdesign @frame_cph

node.text:
The Origami Family is a joyful exploration of handmade craft, bringing together the meticulous, thoughtful work of @claravonzweigbergk and the playful world of HAY.
 
Purchase this limited-edition launch exclusively at HAY House from tomorrow, 16 September.

HAY House 
Østergade 61, Copenhagen

#HAY #HAYdesign

node.text:
Introducing The Origami Family, a collection of origami figures created by Swedish designer @claravonzweigbergk in collaboration with HAY. These pieces, all handmade by von Zweibergk herself, will be available for a limited time only, launching 16 September during @3daysofdesign and sold exclusively at HAY House (Copenhagen).

#HAY #HAYdesign

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by HAY on September 15, 2021.

node.text:
Launching tomorrow: The Origami Family. A limited-edition collection of origami figures created by Swedish designer @claravonzweigbergk in collaboration with HAY. They will be sold from tomorrow exclusively at HAY House in Copenhagen, and will be available while stock lasts.

As supplies are limited, we want to give two Instagram followers the chance to win two members of The Origami Family (medium size). All you need to do is like this post and leave a comment. We will reach out to two winners via DM on 20 September and send two figures to each winner, one for the winner and one to gift to a family member or a friend.

Kindly note that this is not an Instagram advert. No purchase necessary to enter. Minimum age to enter is 18. Open to residents in the EU and the US only. Retail price of medium figure is 549 DKK. Winners selected randomly and contacted via DM. Winners must reply to the DM no later than 24 hours later after being contacted by HAY to confirm the delivery of the prize, which will be arranged by HAY. See link in bio for full terms & conditions.

#HAY #HAYdesign
